#16902
{BOLD}{BLACK}The Bane of the Black Sword{bold}{black}~
{CYAN}
   Elric, having narrowly missed his chance for vengeance, left 
   the Eternal City and began his search anew.  Many years have 
   passed now since the sacking of Imrryr at his own hands.  
   Elric, proud and disdainful in his knowledge that even his 
   deficient blood was the blood of the Sorcerer Kings of 
   Melnibone, became detached.  He had no loyalties, nor 
   friends, and if evil possessed him, it was a pure brilliant evil, 
   untainted by human drivings.

   You follow a deep forest path not far from Bakshaan.  It has 
   been  rumored that the sorcerer of Pan Tang, Theleb K'aarna, 
   has put up residence there.  The forest path meanders softly 
   through the lushly vegetated flora and the ground is still moist 
   from the falling of the morning rain.  It is sad that there is 
   such foul work to be done, and you are quite sure it is not to 
   be taken on lightly by the weak of  heart.

~
