#16912
{BLUE}A Deserted Island Shore{blue}~
{CYAN}
   As the mist clears a landscape of dense shadows is revealed.  
   The shadows spread over red rock and yellow vegetation, and 
   they are shadows of all shapes and dimensions, resembling all 
   manner of things.  They seem cast by the huge blood colored 
   sun which stands at perpetual noon above the island, but what 
   is disturbing about them is that the shadows themselves seem 
   without a source, as if the objects they represent are invisible 
   or existed elsewhere than on the island itself.  They sky, too, 
   seems full of these shadows, but whereas those on the island 
   were still, those in the sky sometimes move, perhaps when  
   the clouds  move.  and all the while the red sun pours down its 
   bloody light and touches you with its unwelcome radiance just 
   as it touches the land.

~
